Tired of not finding clothing she liked in stores, she simply decided to make her own from discarded fabrics. This small step soon led her to the prestigious Studio Berçot fashion school, fashion internships in Paris, and in 1989 launching her eponymous collection. Always basing her creations on her own tastes and trying on every piece before it leaves the studio, all of Isabel Marant clothing and shoes embody her signature style—which blends ease with an elevated feel and a bohemian touch. Creating everything from cowboy boots to statement jewelry and denim jackets, Isabel Marant has become a coveted closet staple for those who want to achieve the same sought-after, Parisian cool-girl look.

Founding Brinker & Eliza in 2017 was a natural step that mined both Brinker’s training as a metalsmith and Eliza’s work in fashion merchandising. With each piece made by hand in the family’s hometown Connecticut studio, Brinker & Eliza jewelry extends that labor of love quality with each of the label’s pieces. Moved by his travels to Africa and encouraged to express his own artistic vision, Gas was met with immediate success on the beaches and shops of Saint-Tropez. Decades later, the family-run GAS Bijoux jewelry label continues to create colorful, imaginative jewelry that reflects the energy and passion of the brand’s founder, while carrying on a tradition of tranquility and vision.

The Dallas native started out studying advertising at the University of Texas—and then changed things up completely, heading to Italy for art courses and to London for sketching and draping at Central Saint Martins. Eventually, after stints at Rebecca Taylor, Ippolita, J.Crew, and Tory Burch, Sadoughi was ready to launch her namesake collection of Lele Sadoughi jewelry. As fun and color-drenched as they are elegant, Lele Sadoughi earrings and rings quickly become the feature of any look—and trust us, with these pieces, that’s exactly what you want.
